The stable, aqueous compositions herein (especially con›
centrated compositions) can also be packaged in a bottle,
especially a bottle that comprises a measuring closure. The
measuring closure provides a convenient means to dispense
the appropriate amount of the composition, especially when
dispensing concentrated compositions into a wash and/or
rinse solution containing fabrics to be treated in a typical
laundry process. The bottle also preferably comprises a
drain-back spout, which permits the composition to be
dispensed more easily and with less mess. Non-limiting
examples of suitable bottles are described in detail in U.S.
